theorem Topology.interior_union_frontier_eq_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    interior (A : Set X) ∪ frontier A = closure A := by
  simpa [frontier] using
    (Topology.interior_union_closureDiffInterior_eq_closure (A := A))

theorem Topology.frontier_subset_closureCompl {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    frontier (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (Aᶜ) := by
  intro x hx
  -- View `hx` as a point on the boundary of `A`.
  have hx_boundary : x ∈ closure (A : Set X) \ interior A := by
    simpa using hx
  -- Apply the previously proven boundary lemma.
  exact (Topology.boundary_subset_closure_compl (A := A)) hx_boundary

theorem Topology.frontier_closureInterior_subset_frontier
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    frontier (closure (interior (A : Set X))) ⊆ frontier A := by
  intro x hx
  -- `hx` gives two facts:
  -- 1. `x ∈ closure (closure (interior A))`
  -- 2. `x ∉ interior (closure (interior A))`
  have hx_closure_int : x ∈ closure (interior A) := by
    -- `closure (closure (interior A))` reduces to `closure (interior A)`.
    simpa [closure_closure] using hx.1
  have hx_not_int_cl : x ∉ interior (closure (interior A)) := hx.2
  -- `x` is also in `closure A`, because `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A`.
  have hx_closureA : x ∈ closure (A : Set X) := by
    have h_sub : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
      closure_mono (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ A)
    exact h_sub hx_closure_int
  -- Show that `x` is *not* in `interior A`. Otherwise we obtain a contradiction.
  have hx_not_intA : x ∉ interior (A : Set X) := by
    intro hx_intA
    -- Since `interior A ⊆ interior (closure (interior A))`,
    -- this would put `x` in `interior (closure (interior A))`,
    -- contradicting `hx_not_int_cl`.
    have h_sub : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure (interior A)) :=
      interior_mono (subset_closure : (interior A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A))
    have : x ∈ interior (closure (interior A)) := h_sub hx_intA
    exact hx_not_int_cl this
  -- Combine the two pieces of information to obtain membership in `frontier A`.
  exact ⟨hx_closureA, hx_not_intA⟩

theorem Topology.interior_diff_subset_left {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A B : Set X) : interior (A \ B : Set X) ⊆ interior A := by
  intro x hx
  -- Since `A \ B ⊆ A`, monotonicity of `interior` yields the claim.
  have h_subset : (A \ B : Set X) ⊆ A := by
    intro y hy
    exact hy.1
  exact (interior_mono h_subset) hx
